# cgroups v2 Compatibility Checker

OpenShift cgroups v2 scanner — Flask web app that scans clusters for container images with cgroups v2 compatibility issues before upgrading to OCP 4.19.

## Tech Stack

- **Backend**: Python 3.11, Flask 3.x, Gunicorn
- **Frontend**: PatternFly 6 (dark theme), vanilla JS (no frameworks)
- **Container**: Podman, UBI 9 base, skopeo for image inspection
- **Platform**: Red Hat OpenShift, deployed via `oc` CLI
- **Registry**: `quay.io/chiaretto/cgroups-v2-checker`

## Architecture

- `app/scanner.py` — Core scan engine (K8s API + skopeo). 3 levels: name/tag analysis, skopeo remote inspection, pod exec runtime detection
- `app/api.py` — REST API (`/api/scan`, `/api/reports`). Scans run async in background thread
- `app/routes.py` — Web routes (HTML pages, CSV download)
- `app/app.py` — Flask factory
- `app/config.py` — Config from env vars
- `app/templates/` — Jinja2, always extend `base.html`
- `app/static/` — PatternFly 6 dark theme CSS, vanilla JS
- `openshift/` — K8s/OCP manifests (Deployment, Service, Route, RBAC)

## Coding Standards

- **Python**: PEP 8, type hints, docstrings on public functions
- **JavaScript**: Vanilla JS only. `var` for compatibility. PatternFly 6 CSS classes (`pf-v6-c-*`)
- **HTML/CSS**: OpenShift Console-style dark theme
- **API**: RESTful JSON under `/api/`

## Build & Deploy

```bash
./setup.sh --build-push-deploy   # Full pipeline
./setup.sh --restart             # Rollout restart
```

## Key Patterns

- Paginated K8s pod listing (`_K8S_PAGE_SIZE = 500`)
- ImagePullSecrets extracted from pods/ServiceAccounts for private registry auth
- Reports stored as JSON in `REPORT_DIR` (default: `/app/data/reports`)
- initContainer-only images get severity downgraded one level
- Test locally: `python run.py` on port 8080
